n ever further into Lesotho's rural upstream catchments: from reservoirs to the soils and vegetation above them, and even to the social lives of herders at remote livestock posts. As we enter our planet's water-export era, Lesotho exposes the possibilities and perils ahead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aWater resources developmentxEnvironmental aspectszLesotho. 0aWater transferzLesotho. 0aWater-supplyzLesotho. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2022 Englishz978311099395008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2022z9783110994186oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520386358zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520386358zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520386358/original  a978-3-11-076649-3 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099395-0 EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-SEWb2022